WEBVTT

00:00.433 --> 00:03.235
Dre:<i> EVERYONE'S GOT</i>
<i>A FAMILY TREE --</i>

00:03.237 --> 00:06.238
<i>A RECORD OF WHO THEY ARE</i>
<i>AND WHERE THEY COME FROM,</i>

00:06.240 --> 00:09.108
<i>ANCIENT BRANCHES</i>
<i>THAT REACH BACK IN TIME</i>

00:09.110 --> 00:11.110
<i>TO THE DEEPEST ROOTS</i>
<i>OF IDENTITY.</i>

00:11.112 --> 00:13.545
<i>OKAY. MAYBE NOT THAT DEEP.</i>

00:13.547 --> 00:15.280
[ SIGHS ]
WE'RE SO GETTING AN "F."

00:15.282 --> 00:17.116
HOPE YOU LOVE
SUMMER SCHOOL, FRIEND.

00:17.118 --> 00:19.251
CAN WE BEEF UP OUR FAMILY TREE
WITH DEAD PETS?

00:19.253 --> 00:23.455
LYLA CHILTON'S FAMILY
CAME HERE ON THE<i> MAYFLOWER.</i>

00:23.457 --> 00:25.591
HEY, YOU TELL YOUR TEACHER
WE SAILED OVER ON A BOAT, TOO.

00:25.593 --> 00:27.192
BUT UNLIKE
LYLA CHILTON'S FAMILY,

00:27.194 --> 00:29.528
WE CAME WITH A RECEIPT.
DRE.

00:29.530 --> 00:34.366
ANY LOVE TO THE HISTORY OF
THE ENSLAVED AND THE OPPRESSED.

00:34.368 --> 00:37.603
ALL WE GET IS A BORING
MINI-SERIES EVERY 400 YEARS.

00:37.605 --> 00:39.271
WELL, BABIES, I KNOW A LOT
ABOUT YOUR HERITAGE.

00:39.273 --> 00:41.774
I ACTUALLY DID
A GENETIC SWAB ONCE.

00:41.776 --> 00:43.442
LET ME SEE IF I STILL
HAVE THAT E-MAIL.
SWAB.

00:43.444 --> 00:46.311
THEY DON'T NEED NO DAMN Q-TIP
TELLING THEM WHERE THEY'RE FROM.

00:46.313 --> 00:50.149
POPS, DNA ANALYSIS IS AMAZING.
YOU GET A WHOLE RUNDOWN.

00:50.151 --> 00:52.151
OH, OH! HERE IT IS.
HERE IT IS.

00:52.153 --> 00:53.485
OKAY, PUT THIS ON MY PART,
OKAY?

00:53.487 --> 00:57.056
23% YORUBA, 19% GAELIC,

00:57.058 --> 01:00.259
AND -- NO DOUBT
FOR SOME HORRIFIC REASON --

01:00.261 --> 01:01.560
1% MONGOL.

01:01.562 --> 01:04.063
HA!
<i>THAT'S</i> WHERE YOU'RE FROM.

01:04.065 --> 01:06.698
A WEIRD,
OLD-TIMEY FIVE SPOT.

01:06.700 --> 01:07.800
MM-HMM.

01:07.802 --> 01:09.768
THANKS,
BUT WE'LL JUST EAT THE "F."

01:09.770 --> 01:13.172
GUESS YOU DON'T WANT TO HEAR
ABOUT HOW YOUR POPS' POPS' POPS

01:13.174 --> 01:15.808
USED THAT TO BET
THE FUTURE OF OUR WHOLE FAMILY

01:15.810 --> 01:17.810
AGAINST A NOTORIOUS
AND RUTHLESS GANGSTER.

01:17.812 --> 01:20.212
A GANGSTER?
OH, NO. GO AHEAD.
GO AHEAD, GO AHEAD.

01:20.214 --> 01:22.614
WATCH ANOTHER ONE OF YOUR
"SpongeBob ShirtPants."

01:22.616 --> 01:24.116
Dre:
OKAY, GUYS. BUCKLE UP.

01:24.118 --> 01:26.452
YOU'RE IN FOR
A REAL POPS SPECIAL.

01:26.454 --> 01:29.621
IT ALL WENT DOWN IN THE YEAR
OF OUR LORD 19 AND 27,

01:29.623 --> 01:31.857
DURING
THE HARLEM RENAISSANCE.

01:31.859 --> 01:34.560
OH, THOSE DUDES
ARE HILARIOUS

01:34.562 --> 01:37.096
WITH THEIR TRICK DUNKS
AND THE CONFETTI BUCKET!

01:37.098 --> 01:39.865
BUT WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT,
BABY BOY, IS A GOLDEN AGE

01:39.867 --> 01:43.235
WHEN BLACK WRITERS
AND ARTISTS AND MUSICIANS

01:43.237 --> 01:47.539
PLANTED OUR CULTURAL FLAG DEEP
IN THE SOUL OF THIS COUNTRY.

01:47.541 --> 01:49.875
Pops:<i> I DON'T MEAN YOUR</i>
<i>GREAT-GREAT-GRANDPA DREXLER.</i>

01:49.877 --> 01:52.377
<i>HE WAS JUST A BUTT-UGLY DOPE</i>
<i>WHO DELIVERED ICE.</i>

01:52.379 --> 01:53.879
<i>LOOKED A LOT LIKE YOUR DAD.</i>

01:53.881 --> 01:59.451
<i>BUT ONE OF HIS REGULAR STOPS</i>
<i>WAS THE LEGENDARY SAVOY CLUB.</i>

01:59.453 --> 02:02.287
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

02:04.791 --> 02:06.425
<i>IT WAS ELECTRIC, CHILDREN.</i>

02:06.860 --> 02:08.861
<i>THE HOTTEST DANCERS</i>
<i>WOWED THEM EVERY NIGHT.</i>

02:10.797 --> 02:15.434
<i>THE GENTS CAME FOR THE DAMES.</i>
<i>THE DAMES CAME FOR THE GAME.</i>

02:16.836 --> 02:18.437
<i>RUNNING IT ALL</i>

02:18.439 --> 02:21.773
<i>A SHREWD AND MOODY GANGSTER --</i>
<i>ELROY SAVOY.</i>

02:21.775 --> 02:24.643
SEND TWO WOMEN AND FOUR BOTTLES
TO THE G-MEN AT TABLE 6,

02:24.645 --> 02:26.145
AND DO SOMETHING
ABOUT THIS MUSIC.

02:26.147 --> 02:28.514
THIS MUSIC IS TERRIBLE.

02:28.516 --> 02:29.848
KEEP IT THE SAME
BUT DIFFERENT.

02:29.850 --> 02:31.783
HEY, ICE BOY.

02:31.785 --> 02:36.655
UH, EXCUSE ME, DID YOU SAY
"ICE BOY" OR "ASS BOY"?

02:36.657 --> 02:37.789
WHAT I SAID IS NEXT TIME
YOU COME THROUGH HERE,

02:37.791 --> 02:39.458
USE THE SERVICE CORRIDOR.

02:39.460 --> 02:41.727
YOU'RE DRIPPING
ALL OVER MY RUG.

02:41.729 --> 02:43.595
I CAUGHT MALARIA IN PERU
LOOKING FOR THIS RUG.

02:43.597 --> 02:45.430
I AIN'T PEED THE SAME
SINCE.

02:45.432 --> 02:47.399
OKAY.

02:47.401 --> 02:49.434
<i>THE ONLY ONE</i>
<i>WHO COULD WARM ELROY</i>

02:49.436 --> 02:52.604
<i>WAS THE SOULFUL SONGBIRD</i>
<i>MIRABELLE CHALET.</i>

02:52.606 --> 02:54.773
HEY, BABY,
YOU LOOKING FINE.

02:54.775 --> 02:56.275
WELL, YOU AIN'T
GOT TO TELL ME THAT.

02:56.277 --> 02:57.776
RIGHT.

02:57.778 --> 03:01.213
BUT SERIOUSLY, I-I --
I DO LOOK GOOD, DON'T I?

03:01.215 --> 03:02.714
YOU LOOK GREAT.

03:02.716 --> 03:04.383
I KNOW, BUT YOU THINK
I NEED TO CHANGE?

03:04.385 --> 03:05.951
'CAUSE I GOT SOMETHING IN
THE BACK THAT'S A LITTLE BETTER.

03:08.688 --> 03:10.789
<i>BUT THE HIPPEST CAT</i>
<i>IN THE JOINT</i>

03:10.791 --> 03:14.660
<i>WAS THE LEGENDARY SPORTS BOOKIE</i>
<i>BIPPY BARNES.</i>

03:14.662 --> 03:16.895
CALL YOU BACK
IN A FEW TICKS, MAC.

03:16.897 --> 03:20.399
DOLLY, GO COLLECT ON THE MARKERS
FROM TODAY'S BANGTAIL RACES.

03:20.401 --> 03:21.567
WITH PLEASURE.

03:21.569 --> 03:24.836
JOLLY,
GO BUY ME A BAG OF BULLETS.

03:24.838 --> 03:26.205
.45s FOR THE TOMMY?

03:26.207 --> 03:27.472
YOU BET
YOUR SWEET BIPPY.

03:28.641 --> 03:29.808
WHERE WERE --

03:29.810 --> 03:30.943
[ DING! ]
Rainbow: HOLD ON.

03:30.945 --> 03:33.445
YOU'RE SAYING,
"YOU BET YOUR SWEET BIPPY"

03:33.447 --> 03:35.681
CAME FROM A BOOKIE
NAMED BIPPY?

03:35.683 --> 03:36.982
WHO'S TELLING THE STORY?

03:36.984 --> 03:38.917
ALL RIGHT. OH.
AND BESIDES,
THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

03:38.919 --> 03:41.286
THE POINT IS THAT
ICE WASN'T THE MAIN REASON

03:41.288 --> 03:42.688
THAT DREX WAS
AT THE SAVOY.

03:42.690 --> 03:44.623
HE WAS THERE FOR BEA.

03:44.625 --> 03:45.657
WHO'S BEA?

03:45.659 --> 03:47.793
ONLY THE LOVE
OF HIS LIFE.

03:47.795 --> 03:49.995
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

03:49.997 --> 03:51.964
<i>A DANCER</i>
<i>WITH LUSTROUS EBONY LOCKS,</i>

03:51.966 --> 03:53.665
<i>THE SMILE OF AN ANGEL,</i>

03:53.667 --> 03:56.702
<i>AND GETAWAY STICKS</i>
<i>THAT WENT ON FOR DAYS.</i>

03:56.704 --> 03:58.870
<i>I ACTUALLY SAW</i>
<i>A PICTURE OF HER ONCE.</i>

03:58.872 --> 04:00.606
SHE LOOKED
JUST LIKE YOUR MAMA.

04:00.608 --> 04:02.741
POPS, THAT DON'T EVEN
MAKE SENSE, MAN.

04:02.743 --> 04:03.775
SHE WASN'T EVEN RELATED
TO BOW --

04:03.777 --> 04:05.777
ZIP IT, ASS BOY.

04:05.779 --> 04:06.912
GO ON, POPS.

04:06.914 --> 04:08.547
THANK YOU, RAINBOW.
MM-HMM.

04:08.549 --> 04:10.315
AND WE'RE OFF.

04:14.921 --> 04:17.022
<i>DREX AND BEA</i>
<i>WERE CRAZY ABOUT EACH OTHER,</i>

04:17.024 --> 04:18.890
<i>BUT THEY REALLY</i>
<i>COULDN'T GO PUBLIC</i>

04:18.892 --> 04:20.892
<i>IN A PLACE THAT STAMPED</i>
<i>BOTH THEIR MEAL TICKETS.</i>

04:20.894 --> 04:21.893
HEY, DREXY. OH! OH!

04:21.895 --> 04:22.894
DREXY.
WHAT?

04:22.896 --> 04:25.030
NOT HERE.
WAY TOO MANY EYES.

04:25.032 --> 04:28.967
I SWEAR, BEA, ONE DAY,
YOU'LL NEVER HAVE TO WORK AGAIN.

04:28.969 --> 04:31.803
JUST A BREEZY LIFE RAISING
OUR 10 CHILDREN,

04:31.805 --> 04:35.741
MENDING OUR CLOTHES,
AND STOMPING ON RATS.

04:35.743 --> 04:36.808
[ GASPS ] RATS.

04:36.810 --> 04:38.343
MM-HMM,
WE GONNA BE RICH.

04:38.345 --> 04:39.578
OH, DREXY -- OH, GOD.

04:39.580 --> 04:41.046
WHAT?
MOON RASH.

04:41.048 --> 04:42.047
OH?

04:42.049 --> 04:44.950
THAT THING'S GONNA TIP OVER
AND KILL ME.

04:44.952 --> 04:46.618
YOU KNOW WHAT, BEA?
HMM?

04:46.620 --> 04:49.621
YOU AND THE REST OF THE GIRLS
SHOULD ORGANIZE INTO A GROUP

04:49.623 --> 04:51.723
AND DEMAND SAFER
WORKING CONDITIONS.

04:51.725 --> 04:53.859
WOW,
I NEVER THOUGHT OF --

04:53.861 --> 04:56.628
YOU'RE SAYING OUR
GREAT-GREAT-GRANDFATHER

04:56.630 --> 04:57.929
INVENTED UNIONS?

04:57.931 --> 04:59.398
WHO'S TELLING THE STORY?

04:59.400 --> 05:01.466
BESIDES, HE DIDN'T
JUST DO IT FOR BEA.

05:01.468 --> 05:02.934
HE DID IT FOR<i> EVERYONE.</i>

05:02.936 --> 05:04.836
LIKE, UH,
ZORA THE COAT-CHECK GIRL

05:04.838 --> 05:07.673
IN HER DANGEROUSLY
UNVENTILATED CLOSET.

05:07.675 --> 05:09.675
THIS WAS
AN EXQUISITE CREATURE --

05:09.677 --> 05:11.543
COPPER-COLORED,
TIMELESS BEAUTY.

05:11.545 --> 05:12.944
SHE LOOKED
A LOT LIKE YOU, ZO-ZO.

05:12.946 --> 05:14.446
CONTINUE.

05:14.448 --> 05:15.447
VERY WELL.

05:15.449 --> 05:17.516
[ TELEGRAPH CLICKING ]

05:19.519 --> 05:20.686
Dre: HI.

05:20.688 --> 05:21.987
YEAH, YEAH.
HOLD YOUR HORSES.

05:21.989 --> 05:23.689
I'LL GET YOUR COAT
IN A JIFF.

05:23.691 --> 05:24.823
I DIDN'T
BRING A COAT.

05:24.825 --> 05:26.525
COAT THIEF, HUH?

05:26.527 --> 05:30.862
YOU CAN PINCH UP TO THREE FURS,
WE'LL SPLIT THE FENCE 50/50.

05:30.864 --> 05:31.997
WHAT? NO, NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO.

05:31.999 --> 05:33.999
I FIGURED A HARDWORKING GIRL
LIKE YOU

05:34.001 --> 05:37.803
STUCK IN THIS SWEAT BOX SMELLING
LIKE DEAD FOX DESERVES SOME ICE.

05:37.805 --> 05:41.606
I'VE BEEN LOOKING TO SCORE
A GOOD DIAMOND HEIST.

05:41.608 --> 05:44.343
[ Chuckling ] BUT --
NO, NOT THAT KIND OF ICE.

05:44.345 --> 05:45.944
ICE, ICE, BABY.

05:45.946 --> 05:48.547
OH...THANKS.

05:48.549 --> 05:49.915
YOU'RE WELCOME.

05:49.917 --> 05:53.452
[ TELEGRAPH CLICKING ]

05:53.454 --> 05:57.689
<i>WHILE THERE MIGHT HAVE BEEN</i>
<i>A RENAISSANCE IN HARLEM,</i>

05:57.691 --> 05:59.891
<i>DOWNTOWN THEY WERE STILL</i>
<i>IN THE DARK AGES.</i>

05:59.893 --> 06:02.928
SO, IN KEEPING WITH
THE TRIUMPHANT PAST CAMPAIGNS

06:02.930 --> 06:08.066
OF KIMBLE, KOLLINS & KLARK,
I GIVE YOU MADSEN COFFEE BEANS.

06:08.068 --> 06:11.069
"MAMMY SAID
YOU LIKE IT DARK."

06:11.071 --> 06:14.072
OUTSTANDING!
NOW YOU'RE ON THE TROLLEY.

06:14.074 --> 06:18.910
BUT I THINK WE SHOULD MAKE THE
SERVANT CHILD A LITTLE DARKER.

06:18.912 --> 06:20.979
I DON'T WANT PEOPLE
MISTAKING HER FOR A MEXICAN.

06:20.981 --> 06:22.147
AH.

06:22.149 --> 06:24.750
SHE SHOULD BE AS DARK AS,
UH...AS HIM.

06:24.752 --> 06:26.785
OOH, THAT'S DARK.

06:26.787 --> 06:28.920
OH, HONORED, SIR...
AND SMART.

06:28.922 --> 06:30.021
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:30.023 --> 06:31.723
THAT'S WHY
YOU'RE THE BIG CHEESE,

06:31.725 --> 06:33.392
AND I LIVE UNDER A TRAIN.

06:33.394 --> 06:34.860
SHALL WE POP
THE BREAKFAST BUBBLY?

06:34.862 --> 06:36.895
OH.
WHY IS THIS STILL WARM?

06:36.897 --> 06:39.164
GENTLEMAN, UH,
SORRY ABOUT THE LATE DELIVERY.

06:39.166 --> 06:40.565
AH, YOUNG DREX.

06:40.567 --> 06:42.801
YOU LOOK A LITTLE MORE
HAGGARD THAN USUAL.

06:42.803 --> 06:45.804
MOONING OVER YOUR DAME ALL NIGHT
AT THE SAVOY AGAIN?

06:45.806 --> 06:48.840
OOH, NOW THAT'S A FROLIC PAD
I'D LIKE TO CUT A RUG AT.

06:48.842 --> 06:52.911
LOVE THAT NEGRO MUSIC AND
NEGRO DANCE AND NEGRO STYLE.

06:52.913 --> 06:54.880
JUST A HUGE NEGRO LOVER.

06:54.882 --> 06:57.582
WOW, YOU REALLY LIKE USING
THAT WORD, HUH?

06:57.584 --> 07:00.485
NOW, I KNOW IT'S THE EXACT RIGHT
WORD FOR OUR TIMES,

07:00.487 --> 07:02.654
BUT, MM,
JUST THE WAY YOU SAY IT.

07:02.656 --> 07:04.656
HEY, JANITOR,
YOU SAY IT.

07:04.658 --> 07:05.991
UH, UH, NEGRO.

07:05.993 --> 07:07.893
SEE. FINE. YOUR TURN.

07:07.895 --> 07:09.895
NEGRO.
WHOO-HOO-HOO.

07:09.897 --> 07:11.830
MAKES MY FISTS BALL UP
EVERY TIME YOU SAY IT.

07:11.832 --> 07:14.966
LISTEN, DREX, IF YOU WANT TO
TAKE IT TO THE NEXT LEVEL

07:14.968 --> 07:16.935
WITH YOUR LITTLE BARLOW...
WHAT?

07:16.937 --> 07:19.137
...YOU GOT TO MAKE HER FEEL LIKE
SHE'S THE CAT'S PAJAMAS.

07:19.139 --> 07:20.772
UH, UH, AND YOU HAVE TO
DRESS TO THE NINES

07:20.774 --> 07:24.943
DREX, LOVE IS ALL
ABOUT OUTWARD APPEARANCE.

07:24.945 --> 07:26.077
CAPITAL IDEA.

07:26.079 --> 07:27.913
I'LL HAVE MY OPIUM GUY
STITCH YOU A SUIT.

07:27.915 --> 07:30.782
BY THE WAY, HE'S ALSO YOUR MAN
FOR IVORY AND PANDA MEAT.

07:30.784 --> 07:31.917
MM!

07:31.919 --> 07:35.954
YOU GENTS EVER WANT TO COME
DOWN TO THE SAVOY, LET ME KNOW.

07:35.956 --> 07:38.023
I GOT AN IN
TO GET YOU A GOOD TABLE.

07:38.025 --> 07:41.726
AH, YOU'RE A SWEET BOY,
BUT, UH, I THINK THAT OUR IN

07:41.728 --> 07:44.996
IS THAT WE'RE INCREDIBLY RICH
AND, UH, ABSURDLY WHITE.

07:44.998 --> 07:46.064
[ LAUGHTER ]

07:48.768 --> 07:51.603
ME --
I'LL NEVER GET INTO SAVOY.

07:51.605 --> 07:53.238
TOO DARK TO PASS
THE PAPER-BAG TEST.

07:53.240 --> 07:56.942
BUT MY OLD ROOMIE, LANGSTON,
GET IN WITH NO PROBLEM.

07:56.944 --> 07:58.877
OLD CARAMEL-COLORED
BASTARD.

07:58.879 --> 08:00.912
NABBED SOME
FANCY BOOK DEAL WRITING

08:00.914 --> 08:03.882
ABOUT RAISINS IN THE SUN --
GOT THAT FROM ME.

08:03.884 --> 08:05.884
LOVE PUTTING STUFF
IN THE SUN --

08:05.886 --> 08:08.887
RAISINS, DAMP SOCKS,
UNCURED BACON.

08:08.889 --> 08:09.888
UH...

08:09.890 --> 08:11.256
IT'S PROBABLY WHY
I'M SO DARK.

08:11.258 --> 08:13.124
[ TELEPHONE RINGING
IN DISTANCE ]

08:13.126 --> 08:17.496
THE SUN, MAN.
THAT CRAZY FIREBALL DON'T PLAY.

08:17.498 --> 08:18.930
[ HORN HONKS IN DISTANCE ]

08:18.932 --> 08:20.832
ALL RIGHT.

08:20.834 --> 08:22.200
YOU STAY LIGHT-SKINNED
OUT THERE, BOY.

08:22.202 --> 08:24.035
[ DING! ]
HOLD ON.

08:24.037 --> 08:26.571
YOU'RE SAYING LANGSTON HUGHES
PLAGIARIZED

08:26.573 --> 08:29.841
AN INSANE JANITOR
WHO LIVED UNDER A TRAIN?

08:29.843 --> 08:34.212
WHO...IS...TELLING...
THIS...STORY?

08:35.681 --> 08:37.682
BESIDES, A LOT OF TRUTH
CAME FROM

08:37.684 --> 08:38.984
A LOT OF POOR FOLKS
WHO NEVER GOT CREDIT.

08:38.986 --> 08:40.852
I'LL GIVE YOU
A "FOR INSTANCE."

08:40.854 --> 08:44.990
BACK IN THE DAY, THERE WAS A
WISE SHOESHINE CALLED JOJO RAGS.

08:44.992 --> 08:46.958
HE WAS KNOWN AS
THE CHILD PROPHET OF HARLEM,

08:46.960 --> 08:49.794
HAD YOUR SAME PRINCELY BEARING
THERE, JUNIOR.

08:49.796 --> 08:52.097
PROCEED.
VERY WELL.

08:52.099 --> 08:53.098
[ HORN HONKING ]

08:53.100 --> 08:54.966
IF YOU ASK JOJO RAGS,

08:54.968 --> 08:57.102
THE STOCK MARKET'S DUE
FOR A BIG TUMBLE.

08:57.104 --> 08:59.971
IF YOU HAVE ANY CABBAGE,
I'D PULL IT OUT LICKETY.

08:59.973 --> 09:03.008
ALSO, I'M PRETTY SURE
GERMANY'S UP TO NO GOOD.

09:03.010 --> 09:05.310
BEEN HEARING ABOUT
SOME BEADY-EYED FRITZ

09:05.312 --> 09:08.647
NAMED ADOLF WHO STOLE
CHARLIE CHAPLIN'S MUSTACHE.

09:08.649 --> 09:10.849
UH, BOY, DO YOU EVER
SHUT YOUR DAMN YAP?

09:10.851 --> 09:13.919
THE ONLY THING THAT SHUTS
JOJO RAGS' YAP IS A GOOD TIP.

09:13.921 --> 09:15.320
FAIR ENOUGH.

09:15.322 --> 09:17.022
[ GRUNTS ]
I GOT TO GO GET MY GIRL.

09:17.024 --> 09:18.657
[ HORN HONKS ]

09:18.659 --> 09:21.860
I'M TELLING YOU, SOMETHING'S
DIFFERENT WITH MY MOON.

09:21.862 --> 09:23.862
IT FEELS LESS...DEADLY.

09:23.864 --> 09:24.963
YOU'RE WELCOME.

09:24.965 --> 09:25.997
WHAT? [ GASPS ]

09:25.999 --> 09:30.001
HELLO,
RUDOLPH VALENTINO.

09:30.003 --> 09:31.202
WHOA, NOT HERE.

09:31.204 --> 09:32.203
OH.
TOO MANY EYES.

09:32.205 --> 09:33.738
[ LAUGHS ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:33.740 --> 09:36.041
WELL, I WOULDN'T WANT IT
FALLING DOWN,

09:36.043 --> 09:38.043
BANGING MY BEA'S KNEES.

09:38.045 --> 09:40.111
AWW, DREXY...
WASN'T NOTHING.

09:40.113 --> 09:42.714
I JUST TOOK SOME MUSIC STANDS
AND SHORED IT UP, THAT'S ALL.

09:42.716 --> 09:44.349
[ LAUGHS ]
HEY, WHERE THE HELL'S
OUR SHEET MUSIC?

09:44.351 --> 09:46.351
OH, HEY, HEY, HEY, MAN,
I'M SORRY.

09:46.353 --> 09:49.321
I'M OVER HERE TRYING TO MAKE
A SAFER WORK ENVIRONMENT.

09:49.323 --> 09:50.889
UH, HEY, WHY DON'T YOU GUYS
IMPROVISE TODAY?

09:50.891 --> 09:53.291
OKAY, DRUM MAN, UH,
GIVE ME A...

09:53.293 --> 09:55.827
♪ TSS, TSS-TSS-TSS,
TSS-TSS-TSS, TSS-TSS-TSS ♪

09:55.829 --> 09:57.829
[ CYMBALS PLAY ]
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH --
LIKE THAT.

09:57.831 --> 09:58.964
BASS MAN.

09:58.966 --> 10:00.932
♪ A-DUM-DUM, DUM-DUM,
DUM-DUM-DUM-DUM ♪

10:00.934 --> 10:02.267
♪ BA-DUM-DUM, DUM-DUM ♪
[ BASS PLAYS ]

10:02.269 --> 10:03.602
[ LAUGHS ]

10:03.604 --> 10:06.037
DIZZY!
BLOW YOUR HORN!

10:06.039 --> 10:07.739
Bea: OH!
[ TRUMPET PLAYS ]

10:07.741 --> 10:10.008
[ LAUGHS ]
YEAH!

10:10.010 --> 10:11.009
[ JAZZ MUSIC PLAYS ]

10:18.117 --> 10:19.884
[ LAUGHS ]
Ruby: EARL JOHNSON!
[ DING! ]

10:19.886 --> 10:24.656
STOP LYING ABOUT HOW YOUR
IDIOT GRANDADDY INVENTED JAZZ.

10:24.658 --> 10:26.358
NEVER SAID JAZZ.
JUST BEATS BY DREX.

10:26.360 --> 10:30.061
[ BOTH LAUGH ]
EVEN HAD THE MEAN, DRUNK,
OLD CLUB MADAM

10:30.063 --> 10:35.000
UH-HUH. YOU'RE NOT EVEN TRYING
TO GREASE MY WHEELS, ARE YOU?

10:35.002 --> 10:36.368
NOPE.

10:36.370 --> 10:40.005
ALL RIGHT, GIRLS, COME ON.
COME ON. COME ON.

10:40.007 --> 10:43.375
LORD KNOWS YOU AIN'T GETTING
ANY YOUNGER OR PRETTIER.

10:43.377 --> 10:45.010
YOU'RE ONE TO TALK.

10:45.012 --> 10:47.278
YOU KNOW, I CAN'T WAIT

10:47.280 --> 10:49.948
TILL SOMEONE SHOVES A ROSCOE
IN YOUR BUTTON

10:49.950 --> 10:52.384
AND BLASTS YOUR GRITS
ALL OVER THE WALLPAPER.

10:52.386 --> 10:54.219
BEAT IT.
UH!

10:54.221 --> 10:56.921
COME ON, GIRLS.
LET'S GET A WIGGLE ON.

10:56.923 --> 10:59.324
LET'S GO!
WHOO! COME ON!

11:02.828 --> 11:05.830
BABE, LISTEN,
I'VE BEEN SAVING UP.

11:05.832 --> 11:06.998
AND I DON'T HAVE
AS MUCH AS I'D LIKE,

11:07.000 --> 11:09.401
BUT ALL WE NEED
IS EACH OTHER, RIGHT?

11:09.403 --> 11:10.969
WHAT ARE YOU GETTING AT,
DREXY?

11:10.971 --> 11:14.439
[ GASPS ] REALLY?
LOOK, AWAY FROM ALL OF THIS.

11:14.441 --> 11:16.307
[ GASPS ]
HEY, WE COULD LEAVE TONIGHT.

11:16.309 --> 11:18.943
OH, MY GOSH.
ASS BOY!

11:18.945 --> 11:20.679
WHAT YOU DOING?

11:20.681 --> 11:21.980
YOU TRYING TO MAKE TIME
WITH MY GIRL?

11:21.982 --> 11:23.815
I-I'M SORRY, MR. SAVOY.

11:23.817 --> 11:24.916
BUT I THOUGHT MIRABELLE
WAS YOUR GIRL.

11:24.918 --> 11:27.752
THEY'RE ALL MY GIRLS.

11:27.754 --> 11:29.354
EXCEPT FOR THAT ONE
RIGHT THERE.

11:29.356 --> 11:31.389
YEAH,
HIT BRICKS, PALOOKA!

11:31.391 --> 11:32.390
HEY!
[ BAND GROANS ]

11:32.392 --> 11:34.025
THAT'S RIGHT.

11:34.027 --> 11:37.362
AND IF I EVER SEE YOU TALKING
WITH ONE OF MY GIRLS AGAIN,

11:37.364 --> 11:40.131
I'M GONNA FILL THAT BELLY
WITH LEAD.

11:40.133 --> 11:44.402
NOW GO PEDDLE SOME ICE,
ASS BOY.

11:46.439 --> 11:50.875
SO, HE CAN
DEFINITELY SAY "ICE."

11:53.245 --> 11:55.980
Dre:<i> SO, POPS' FISH TALE HAD</i>
<i>TAKEN A LOT OUT OF HIM.</i>

11:55.982 --> 11:57.449
[ SNORES ]

11:57.451 --> 11:58.917
COME ON, POPS! WAKE UP!
HUH?

11:58.919 --> 12:01.886
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
HOW LONG WAS I OUT?

12:01.888 --> 12:03.288
NOT LONG ENOUGH.

12:03.290 --> 12:05.290
I WANT TO HEAR HOW
GREAT-GREAT-GRANDPA DREX

12:05.292 --> 12:07.459
SAVED HIS SWEET HONEY BEA
FROM ELROY SAVOY.

12:07.461 --> 12:09.461
MY MONEY'S
ON JOJO RAGS.

12:09.463 --> 12:12.330
SERIOUSLY?
DUDE HAS "RAGS" IN HIS NAME.

12:12.332 --> 12:17.302
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]
NO ONE'S TEXTING,
POSTING, STREAMING.

12:17.304 --> 12:19.971
THEY'RE JUST LISTENING
ABOUT THEIR FAMILY.

12:19.973 --> 12:21.506
MM.

12:21.508 --> 12:23.007
THINGS WERE DIRE, CHILDREN,
VERY DIRE.

12:23.009 --> 12:25.343
SEE, DREX KNEW
WITH ELROY IN HIS WAY,

12:25.345 --> 12:27.045
HE COULD NEVER BE
WITH BEA.

12:27.047 --> 12:29.914
AND NO ONE COULD SING
OF HEARTBREAK

12:29.916 --> 12:32.884
BETTER THAN
MIRABELLE CHALET.

12:32.886 --> 12:35.120
[ "I'M GOIN' DOWN" PLAYS ]

12:37.523 --> 12:43.194
♪ TIME ON MY HANDS
SINCE YOU BEEN AWAY, BOY ♪

12:43.196 --> 12:47.499
♪ I AIN'T GOT NO PLANS ♪

12:47.501 --> 12:49.968
♪ NO, NO, NO, NO ♪

12:53.272 --> 12:58.977
♪ AND THE SOUND OF
THE RAIN AGAINST MY WINDOWPANE ♪

12:58.979 --> 13:01.112
♪ IS SLOWLY ♪

13:01.114 --> 13:05.450
♪ IS SLOWLY DRIVING ME INSANE ♪

13:05.452 --> 13:10.288
♪ BOY, I'M GOING DOWN ♪

13:10.290 --> 13:12.924
♪ I'M GOING DOWN ♪

13:12.926 --> 13:16.961
♪ 'CAUSE YOU AIN'T AROUND ♪

13:16.963 --> 13:24.969
♪ BABY, MY WHOLE WORLD'S
UPSIDE DOWN ♪

13:24.971 --> 13:26.805
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

13:26.807 --> 13:27.972
♪ OOH, BABY, LOVE ♪

13:27.974 --> 13:30.809
I'VE SUNG THAT SONG
2,000 TIMES.

13:30.811 --> 13:33.411
AND EVERY TIME,
ALL EYES WAS ON ME.

13:33.413 --> 13:36.414
BUT YOU DIDN'T TAKE YOUR EYES
OFF BEA FOR A SECOND.

13:36.416 --> 13:38.449
MAN, I WISH SOMEONE
LOVED ME LIKE THAT.

13:38.451 --> 13:39.551
WHAT ABOUT ELROY?

13:39.553 --> 13:41.553
ELROY LOVES ELROY.

13:41.555 --> 13:43.054
OH, AND HOBO FIGHTS.

13:43.056 --> 13:46.958
BUT WHAT YOU GOT, MAN --
WHAT YOU GOT IS SPECIAL,

13:46.960 --> 13:48.827
SO FIGHT FOR HER.

13:48.829 --> 13:50.995
[ SCOFFS ]
THIS CHUMP?

13:50.997 --> 13:52.030
ELROY'S BOYS

13:52.032 --> 13:54.065
WILL CHOP HIM UP
AND SPIT HIM OUT

13:54.067 --> 13:56.000
LIKE CHEAP CAROLINA LEAF.
MM-HMM.

13:56.002 --> 13:58.002
LOOK, Y'ALL DON'T HAVE TO
BEAT ELROY'S THUGS,

13:58.004 --> 14:00.038
JUST THAT BIG,
SWOLLEN HEAD OF HIS.

14:00.040 --> 14:02.273
HE THINK HE CAN DANCE,
BUT LOOK.

14:02.275 --> 14:04.342
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

14:09.114 --> 14:10.515
THAT AIN'T
HIS ONLY WEAKNESS.

14:10.517 --> 14:12.016
THE MAN IS
A DEGENERATE GAMBLER.

14:12.018 --> 14:13.518
ALSO,
YOU COULD PLAY THAT ANGLE.

14:13.520 --> 14:15.420
SO NOW YOU BELIEVE IN ME?
NOT AT ALL.

14:15.422 --> 14:17.589
I JUST DON'T LIKE THE WAY
THIS BOY ELROY OPERATES --

14:17.591 --> 14:18.923
NO HONOR.

14:18.925 --> 14:20.925
BY MY BOOK,
WHEN YOU BUMP A GUY,

14:20.927 --> 14:23.094
AT LEAST HAVE THE DECENCY
TO CHOP HIM UP IN LITTLE PIECES,

14:23.096 --> 14:24.295
THEN THROW HIM
IN THE RIVER.

14:24.297 --> 14:26.865
ELROY -- HE SHOOTS YOU
IN THE BACK

14:26.867 --> 14:29.334
AND LEAVES YOU IN AN ALLEY
FOR CATS TO EAT YOUR FACE.

14:29.336 --> 14:32.437
DON'T EVEN HAVE THE CLASS TO
BARNEYMUG YOUR BEREAVED WOMAN.

14:32.439 --> 14:36.007
WHAT?
WELL, THANK YOU.
REALLY GOOD PEP TALK.

14:36.009 --> 14:38.176
ALL I'M SAYING IS
BETWEEN ELROY'S UNLUCKY HAND

14:38.178 --> 14:40.879
AND TWO LEFT FEET, YOU STAND
A CHANCE AT TAKING HIM DOWN.

14:40.881 --> 14:42.547
COME ON, DREX.
DON'T LET LOVE DIE.

14:42.549 --> 14:44.616
GO GET YOUR GIRL.

14:44.618 --> 14:48.019
DAMN IT.
YOU'RE RIGHT.

14:51.223 --> 14:53.524
CATS ARE GONNA
EAT HIS FACE.

14:53.526 --> 14:54.659
THE DOGS, TOO.

14:54.661 --> 14:57.328
NO, I GOT IT, BEA.
NO, BEA.
DREXY!

14:57.330 --> 15:00.031
AND THE SECURITY TRIES --
EXCUSE ME, MR. SAVOY.
WE NEED TO CONFABULATE.

15:00.033 --> 15:02.033
I'M IN LOVE WITH BEA,
BEA'S IN LOVE WITH ME,

15:02.035 --> 15:03.501
AND WE WANT TO SPEND
THE REST OF OUR LIVES TOGETHER.

15:03.503 --> 15:05.603
BOOM!

15:05.605 --> 15:07.038
ALL I GOT
IN THIS WORLD.

15:07.040 --> 15:08.973
5 BUCKS?
MM-HMM.

15:08.975 --> 15:10.341
DREXY, I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU'VE BEEN SAVING UP.

15:10.343 --> 15:11.943
I WAS EXPECTING YOU
TO PUT DOWN AN ABRAHAM.

15:11.945 --> 15:15.079
IT'S FINE. BUT GOING FORWARD,
I'M GONNA DO THE BOOKKEEPING.
OKAY, YOU GOT IT.

15:15.081 --> 15:16.514
GO AHEAD, GO AHEAD, GO AHEAD.
ALL RIGHT.

15:16.516 --> 15:19.984
ELROY SAVOY,
I CHALLENGE YOU TO A DANCE DUEL.

15:19.986 --> 15:22.987
[ CHUCKLES ]
AND IF I WIN,
YOU LET BEA OUT OF HER CONTRACT

15:22.989 --> 15:24.455
AND YOU LEAVE US ALONE
FOREVER.

15:24.457 --> 15:28.059
BUT IF YOU WIN,
YOU GET MY LIFE SAVINGS.

15:28.061 --> 15:31.396
OH, YOU KNOW
I LOVE TO DANCE!

15:31.398 --> 15:33.531
ICE BOY, YOU ON.

15:33.533 --> 15:35.533
MM.
BUT ONE THING --

15:35.535 --> 15:37.235
I'M GONNA USE
THIS PROXY DANCER.

15:37.237 --> 15:39.370
WHAT?
SEE, I'VE BEEN
RECENTLY INFORMED

15:39.372 --> 15:43.074
THAT I'M A HORRIBLE HOOFER,
BY MY BROTHER.

15:43.076 --> 15:44.208
MAY HE REST IN PEACE.

15:44.210 --> 15:46.978
ME? DANCE FOR YOU?

15:46.980 --> 15:49.247
I'M LOYAL TO BIPPY
TILL THE DAY I DIE.

15:49.249 --> 15:51.082
HERE'S A NICKEL.

15:51.084 --> 15:53.184
BIPPY'S DEAD TO ME.

15:53.186 --> 15:55.453
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

15:55.455 --> 15:56.721
OW.

15:56.723 --> 15:58.389
YEAH, I'M GONNA DIE
ON THAT MOON.

16:01.127 --> 16:09.968
DREX "THE ICE MAN COMETH"
vs. JOLLY "THE JUMPING RUNNER."

16:09.970 --> 16:13.604
TIME TO SET THE STAGE
FOR THE SVOY SALVO!

16:13.606 --> 16:16.975
[ APPLAUSE ]
BETS HERE. PLACE YOUR BETS HERE.

16:16.977 --> 16:18.609
WHY DON'T YOU GET UP
AND DO SOME SQUATS?

16:18.611 --> 16:22.246
I ONCE HAD SCURVY
AND CURRENTLY HAVE RICKETS.

16:22.248 --> 16:24.282
AND YET,
YOU CHOSE A DANCE BATTLE?

16:24.284 --> 16:26.517
I -- WELL, I --
NEVER MIND. NEVER MIND.

16:26.519 --> 16:28.186
JUST GO OUT THERE
AND DO YOU BEST.
MM-HMM.

16:28.188 --> 16:30.054
AND KNOW THAT
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,

16:30.056 --> 16:32.056
I WILL ALWAYS
REMEMBER YOU.

16:32.058 --> 16:33.524
OKAY. UH...

16:33.526 --> 16:34.993
WHAT?

16:34.995 --> 16:36.294
BOYS, THROW ME
A BEAT FOR HOT FEET!

16:36.296 --> 16:38.529
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

16:47.106 --> 16:49.107
[ MUSIC STOPS ]
[ APPLAUSE ]

16:49.109 --> 16:51.509
IS IT ME?
LET'S GO. OKAY.

16:51.511 --> 16:55.146
I GOT THIS. ALL RIGHT, UH...
GIVE ME A SHIMMY.

16:55.148 --> 16:57.115
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

17:02.021 --> 17:04.789
THAT'S MY MAN.

17:06.058 --> 17:07.058
[ MUSIC STOPS ]
HA!

17:07.060 --> 17:08.559
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

17:08.561 --> 17:09.727
BRING THE SWING!

17:09.729 --> 17:11.763
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

17:26.812 --> 17:29.047
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

17:29.049 --> 17:31.149
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

17:34.086 --> 17:35.053
ALL RIGHT. YOU READY?

17:35.055 --> 17:36.587
UH, UH, HEY, BAND.

17:36.589 --> 17:39.257
WHY DON'T YOU JUST GO
AND GIVE ME -- OW!
OH! AAH! DREXY!

17:39.259 --> 17:40.358
DREXY!

17:40.360 --> 17:41.692
OHH,
I SLIPPED ON SOMETHING.

17:41.694 --> 17:43.494
HUH?
[ GASPS ]

17:43.496 --> 17:45.830
ICE. OH, THE IRONY.

17:45.832 --> 17:48.533
OH, NO.
I CAN'T LET SAVOY WIN.

17:48.535 --> 17:50.201
BUT YOU CAN'T STAND UP.

17:50.203 --> 17:52.537
MAYBE I DON'T HAVE TO.

17:52.539 --> 17:54.539
REALLY? OKAY.
UH-HUH. BAND.

17:54.541 --> 17:57.375
♪ TSS, TSS-TSS-TSS,
TSS-TSS-TSS ♪

17:57.377 --> 17:58.443
[ JAZZ MUSIC PLAYS ]

18:02.181 --> 18:04.615
WHOO!
UH...OKAY.

18:04.617 --> 18:07.785
[ CROWD GASPS ]

18:14.426 --> 18:15.526
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

18:15.528 --> 18:17.829
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

18:17.831 --> 18:21.132
TURN IT UP! HA HA!
HA HA!

18:21.134 --> 18:22.300
YEAH!
HA HA!

18:22.302 --> 18:23.301
AAH! AAH!

18:23.303 --> 18:27.605
HE BEAT JOLLY BY INVENTING
BREAK-DANCING?!

18:27.607 --> 18:29.107
NOPE. I REJECT THAT.

18:29.109 --> 18:31.876
DON'T BE A SORE MORON.
OUR FAMILY WON!

18:31.878 --> 18:33.678
ACTUALLY...

18:33.680 --> 18:34.846
DISQUALIFIED?!

18:34.848 --> 18:36.747
I DIDN'T AGREE TO
NO WORM-LIKE DANCING.

18:36.749 --> 18:38.749
I'M GONNA RIP HIS HEAD OFF.
NO, BEA. BEA, BEA.

18:38.751 --> 18:40.618
DANCING LIKE A WORM.

18:40.620 --> 18:42.787
WE CAN STILL BUY BACK
YOUR CONTRACT.

18:42.789 --> 18:44.122
MY BANK
DON'T TAKE ICE CHIPS.

18:44.124 --> 18:46.124
[ LAUGHTER ]
OH. TOO BAD.

18:46.126 --> 18:48.126
HOW ABOUT THE TWO GRAND
I MADE THROUGH BIPPY

18:48.128 --> 18:49.527
BETTING AGAINST MYSELF?

18:49.529 --> 18:50.695
THAT'S RIGHT.

18:50.697 --> 18:52.130
I DIDN'T TRUST YOU,

18:52.132 --> 18:54.265
SO I HEDGED MY CHANCES TO WIN
EVEN IF I LOST.

18:54.267 --> 18:55.500
HA!

18:55.502 --> 18:56.801
KILL HIM.

18:56.803 --> 18:58.870
HEY -- RUN!
LET'S GO! LET'S GO!
RUN! RUN!

18:58.872 --> 19:01.772
MOVE YOUR RICKETY LEGS! GO!
OH, THEY'RE RICKETY,
RICKETY, RICKETY!

19:01.774 --> 19:03.608
THE KID -- THE KID TIED
MY SHOES TO THE -- TO THE --

19:03.610 --> 19:05.877
THE KID TIED -- THE KID TIED
MY SHOES TO THE TABLE.

19:05.879 --> 19:07.912
RUN!
GO, GO!

19:07.914 --> 19:10.414
NOW, WHAT I WAS JUST TRYING TO
SAY TO Y'ALL BEFORE

19:10.416 --> 19:14.252
IS I'M THINKING ABOUT STARTING
THIS LINE OF LINGERIE --

19:14.254 --> 19:16.187
SAVOY JAVOY.

19:16.189 --> 19:18.589
YOU LIKE THAT?

19:18.591 --> 19:20.424
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT!
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT!

19:20.426 --> 19:22.260
WE GOT TO GET MY COAT.
OH, TO HELL WITH IT!

19:22.262 --> 19:23.761
NO, NO, THE ONLY REASON
I'M DOWN TO $5

19:23.763 --> 19:25.663
IS BECAUSE YOUR WEDDING RING
IS IN THERE!

19:25.665 --> 19:28.166
WE GOT TO GET YOUR COAT.
OKAY, LET'S GO. OH!

19:28.168 --> 19:30.334
DRAT.
ONE OF ELROY'S GOONS.

19:30.336 --> 19:33.204
[ TELEGRAPH CLICKING ]

19:33.206 --> 19:35.206
HOLD ON A SEC.

19:35.208 --> 19:37.708
[ TELEGRAPH CLICKING ]

19:37.710 --> 19:39.844
HERE SHE COMES.

19:42.214 --> 19:44.348
COME ON. COME ON. COME ON.
COME ON, COAT CHECK.

19:44.350 --> 19:45.917
GO! GO!

19:45.919 --> 19:48.186
UH, GO SHOW THEM
MY EMERGENCY ESCAPE ROUTE.

19:48.188 --> 19:49.687
BUT HE JUST WON
A HUGE BET OFF YOU.

19:49.689 --> 19:51.822
EXACTLY. HE GETS AWAY,
BIPPY DON'T HAVE TO PAY.

19:51.824 --> 19:53.357
THEY'RE GONNA NEED
FAST WHEELS.

19:53.359 --> 19:55.359
GIVE THEM THESE.

19:55.361 --> 19:58.696
HEY, AWFUL NICE GIVING UP
YOUR BREEZER, BIPPY.

19:58.698 --> 20:00.264
YOU GETTING SOFT?

20:00.266 --> 20:02.833
THAT WAS THE KEY
TO<i> YOUR</i> CAR.

20:02.835 --> 20:05.870
[BLEEP]

20:05.872 --> 20:08.873
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

20:08.875 --> 20:10.541
GET IN THE CAR!
GET IN THE CAR!

20:10.543 --> 20:12.743
[ BOTH PANTING ]

20:12.745 --> 20:15.780
THANK YOU, GUYS.
RISKING YOUR LIVES TO SAVE US.

20:15.782 --> 20:16.948
I JUST HATE ELROY.

20:16.950 --> 20:18.749
THAT CLOWN'S
A WORSE TIPPER THAN YOU.

20:18.751 --> 20:21.886
YOUR PARENTS,
THEY RAISED YOU RIGHT.

20:21.888 --> 20:23.254
WE'RE ALL ORPHANS.

20:23.256 --> 20:25.523
AWKWARD.

20:25.525 --> 20:27.858
WELL...UH...

20:27.860 --> 20:29.260
WE...WE CAN'T
LEAVE THEM HERE.

20:29.262 --> 20:30.695
NO.
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

20:30.697 --> 20:32.863
WELL, YOU'RE NOT ORPHANS
ANYMORE.

20:32.865 --> 20:33.931
GET IN THE CAR!

20:33.933 --> 20:35.533
AAH! YAY! YAY!

20:35.535 --> 20:37.668
SHOTGUN!
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:37.670 --> 20:38.903
WE'RE NOT ORPHANS!
[ GUN COCKS ]

20:41.673 --> 20:43.674
AND THAT IS
THE GOD'S HONEST TRUTH.

20:43.676 --> 20:45.443
Diane: [ GASPS ] WOW!

20:45.445 --> 20:47.245
SO, THEY KEPT
THE PLUCKY ORPHANS?

20:47.247 --> 20:48.679
YEAH, AT LEAST TILL THE
SPANISH FLU WIPED THEM ALL OUT.

20:48.681 --> 20:50.414
[ BOTH GASP ]
[ CHUCKLES ] JUST KIDDING.

20:50.416 --> 20:51.749
[ LAUGHS ]

20:51.751 --> 20:53.851
NO, THEY ALL BECAME
THE GREAT AUNTS AND UNCLES

20:53.853 --> 20:55.853
THAT YOU'RE ALL
NAMED AFTER.

20:55.855 --> 20:57.855
[ CHUCKLES ]
Jack: SO AWESOME!

20:57.857 --> 21:00.258
DIANE, MAKE SURE TO PUT
THAT UNCLE JOJO RAGS

21:00.260 --> 21:03.861
PREDICTED THE GREAT DEPRESSION
AND WORLD WAR II.
YES!

21:03.863 --> 21:06.797
WHATEVER.
AUNT ZORA INVENTED TEXTING.

21:06.799 --> 21:08.799
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
EVERYBODY LISTEN UP.

21:08.801 --> 21:11.802
LISTEN UP, LISTEN UP.

21:11.804 --> 21:13.871
<i>I'VE</i> GOT A STORY TO TELL.

21:13.873 --> 21:15.039
I BET YOU DO.

21:15.041 --> 21:17.908
IT'S ABOUT YOUR
GREAT-GREAT-GREAT-GRANDMA,

21:17.910 --> 21:21.412
AUNT...JEMIMA.

21:21.414 --> 21:25.783
OH, SHE WAS BIG, SHE WAS BLACK,
AND SHE WAS BEAUTIFUL --

21:25.785 --> 21:28.052
A LOT LIKE
YOUR GRANDMA RUBY.

21:28.054 --> 21:31.055
[ BOTH LAUGH ]
<i>SO, THE TWINS HAD</i>
<i>PLENTY OF INFORMATION</i>

21:31.057 --> 21:32.490
<i>FOR THEIR FAMILY-HISTORY</i>
<i>PROJECT.</i>

21:32.492 --> 21:34.292
<i>WOULD THEIR TEACHER BUY IT?</i>

21:34.294 --> 21:36.460
DO YOU THINK
THIS IS A JOKE?

21:36.462 --> 21:38.629
<i>NOT AT ALL. THEY GOT THE "F."</i>

21:38.631 --> 21:41.899
<i>BUT POINT IS,</i>
<i>THERE IS A STORY TO TELL --</i>

21:41.901 --> 21:45.970
<i>THE STORY OF US,</i>
<i>OUR FAMILY, OUR CULTURE.</i>

21:45.972 --> 21:48.973
<i>THE DETAILS OF THE STORY</i>
<i>MIGHT CHANGE OVER TIME,</i>

